This is the "summer" version 
It adds beeswax because coconut oil creates a mess on the counter with it's really low melting point. I use it year round because Texas. I have a friend who doesn't want to mess with the wax so she keeps it in the refrigerator.

2 tbs beeswax
1/4 c coconut oil
1/4 c cornsarch
1/4 c baking soda

Melt beeswax in double boiler (or very low heat) add coconut oil and other ingredients. Have to add before mixture hardens.

You can add tea tree oil since it's an anti bacterial but some people don't like the smell. 

My "double boiler" is just a ceramic bowl on a little sauce pot. 

Too much wax makes it too hard so be careful.

God is our priority if we are Christians.
